project/
├── app/                     # Core application directory
│   ├── config/              # Configuration files
│   │   ├── bootstrap.php
│   │   ├── config.php
│   │   ├── routes.php
│   │   └── services.php
│   ├── controllers/         # Controllers for handling business logic
│   │   └── UserController.php
│   ├── models/              # Models for database interaction
│   │   ├── Habitations.php
│   │   ├── Reservation.php
│   │   └── Users.php
│   └── views/               # Views for displaying HTML
│       ├── admin/
│       │   ├── base.php
│       │   ├── footer.php
│       │   ├── head.php
│       │   ├── header.php
│       │   └── sidebar.php
│       └── clients/
│           ├── base.php
│           ├── footer.php
│           ├── head.php
│           ├── header.php
│           ├── home.php
│           ├── login.php
│           ├── register.php
│           └── swipe.php
├── database/                # Base de donnees
│   ├── data.sql
│   ├── drop.sql
│   └── schema.sql
├── public/                  # Publicly accessible directory (entry point)
│   ├── .htaccess            # Apache configuration for routing (if using Apache)
│   ├── index.php            # Main application entry point
└── vendor/                  # Composer dependencies (after `composer install`)
├── .env                     # Environment variables (database credentials, etc.)
├── composer.json            # Composer file for managing dependencies
├── composer.lock            # Lock file for Composer
└── README.md                # Project documentation
└── todo                     # Todo list






Directory and File Descriptions
public/

This is the public-facing directory where your application begins.
index.php is the entry point that initializes Flight and loads routes.
app/controllers/

Contains controllers that process requests and return appropriate responses.
Example:
VehicleController.php handles routes for vehicle-related logic, like listing available vehicles or calculating benefits.
app/models/

Contains models that interact with the database.
Example:
Vehicle.php fetches data about vehicles from the vehicles table.
app/views/

Contains views that render HTML for the browser.
Organized into subdirectories (vehicles/, trips/) based on functionality.
app/config/

Contains configuration files.
database.php: Sets up the database connection using PDO.
settings.php: Stores global settings, such as salary percentages.
vendor/

Directory for Composer dependencies. It will be created after running composer install.
.env

Stores environment-specific variables like database credentials, which are loaded using a library like vlucas/phpdotenv.


Lunch port 8000
->php -S localhost:8000
